pipeline_summary.name: Content Moderation Pipeline
pipeline_summary.description: Comprehensive pipeline that scans usergenerated content for toxicity, branches based on a 0.7 threshold, and merges results for audit logging.

components.name: Extract User Content
components.description: Reads the user-generated content CSV file and emits metadata (total item count and file path) via XCom.

connections.purpose: Read CSV file from local storage

components.name: Evaluate Toxicity
components.description: Computes a toxicity score for the extracted content and returns a branch decision based on a 0.7 threshold.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after successful extraction of user content.

components.name: Remove and Flag Toxic Content
components.description: Deletes toxic content from the platform and flags the associated user accounts for review.

upstream_policy.description: Executed when the toxicity check routes to the hightoxicity branch.

connections.purpose: Interact with the platform content management system to delete content and flag users

components.name: Publish Safe Content
components.description: Publishes nontoxic user content to the platform for visibility.

upstream_policy.description: Executed when the toxicity check routes to the lowtoxicity branch.

connections.purpose: Publish content to the userfacing platform

components.name: Audit Log Consolidation
components.description: Creates a consolidated audit log entry capturing outcomes from both removal and publishing branches.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after both branch paths have completed, regardless of which branch was taken.
